      • CONTINUOUS_FRAMEWORK

        public static final URI CONTINUOUS_FRAMEWORK
        Modelling approach where the quantities of participants are considered continuous, and represented by real values (SBO:0000062). The associated simulation methods make use of differential equations.

      • NON_SPATIAL_CONTINUOUS_FRAMEWORK

        public static final URI NON_SPATIAL_CONTINUOUS_FRAMEWORK
        Modelling approach where the quantities of participants are considered continuous, and represented by real values (SBO:0000293). The associated simulation methods make use of differential equations. The models do not take into account the distribution of the entities and describe only the temporal fluxes.

      • SPATIAL_CONTINUOUS_FRAMEWORK

        public static final URI SPATIAL_CONTINUOUS_FRAMEWORK
        Modelling approach where the quantities of participants are considered continuous, and represented by real values (SBO:0000292). The associated simulation methods make use of differential equations. The models take into account the distribution of the entities and describe the spatial fluxes.

      • DISCRETE_FRAMEWORK

        public static final URI DISCRETE_FRAMEWORK
        Modelling approach where the quantities of participants are considered discrete, and represented by integer values (SBO:0000063). The associated simulation methods can be deterministic or stochastic.

      • NON_SPATIAL_DISCRETE_FRAMEWORK

        public static final URI NON_SPATIAL_DISCRETE_FRAMEWORK
        Modelling approach where the quantities of participants are considered discrete, and represented by integer values (SBO:0000295). The associated simulation methods can be deterministic or stochastic.The models do not take into account the distribution of the entities and describe only the temporal fluxes.

      • SPATIAL_DISCRETE_FRAMEWORK

        public static final URI SPATIAL_DISCRETE_FRAMEWORK
        Modelling approach where the quantities of participants are considered discrete, and represented by integer values (SBO:0000294). The associated simulation methods can be deterministic or stochastic. The models take into account the distribution of the entities and describe the spatial fluxes.

      • FLUX_BALANCE_FRAMEWORK

        public static final URI FLUX_BALANCE_FRAMEWORK
        Modelling approach, typically used for metabolic models, where the flow of metabolites (flux) through a network can be calculated (SBO:0000624). This approach will generally produce a set of solutions (solution space), which may be reduced using objective functions and constraints on individual fluxes.

        public static final URI BIOLOGICAL_EFFECT_OF_A_PERTURBATION
        Biochemical networks can be affected by external influences (SBO:0000357). Those influences can be well-defined physical perturbations, such as a light pulse, or a change in temperature but also more complex of not well defined phenomena, for instance a biological process, an experimental setup, or a mutation.

      • COMPOSITE_BIOCHEMICAL_PROCESS

        public static final URI COMPOSITE_BIOCHEMICAL_PROCESS
        Process that involves the participation of chemical or biological entities and is composed of several elementary steps or reactions (SBO:0000205).

      • DNA_REPLICATION

        public static final URI DNA_REPLICATION
        Process in which a DNA duplex is transformed into two identical DNA duplexes (SBO:0000204).

      • GENETIC_PRODUCTION

        public static final URI GENETIC_PRODUCTION
        A composite biochemical process through which a gene sequence is fully converted into mature gene products (SBO:0000589). These gene products may include RNA species as well as proteins, and the process encompasses all intermediate steps required to generate the active form of the gene product.

      • TRANSCRIPTION

        public static final URI TRANSCRIPTION
        Process through which a DNA sequence is copied to produce a complementary RNA (SBO:0000183).

      • TRANSLATION

        public static final URI TRANSLATION
        Process in which a polypeptide chain is produced from a messenger RNA (SBO:0000184).

      • ENCAPSULATING_PROCESS

        public static final URI ENCAPSULATING_PROCESS
        An aggregation of interactions and entities into a single process (SBO:0000395).

      • MOLECULAR_OR_GENETIC_INTERACTION

        public static final URI MOLECULAR_OR_GENETIC_INTERACTION
        Mutual or reciprocal action or influence between molecular entities (SBO:0000342).

      • GENETIC_INTERACTION

        public static final URI GENETIC_INTERACTION
        A phenomenon whereby an observed phenotype, qualitative or quantative, is not explainable by the simple additive effects of the individual gene pertubations alone (SBO:0000343). Genetic interaction between perturbed genes is usually expected to generate a 'defective' phenotype. The level of defectiveness is often used to sub-classify this phenomenon.

      • GENETIC_ENHANCEMENT

        public static final URI GENETIC_ENHANCEMENT
        Genetic enhancement is said to have occurred when the phenotypic effect of an initial mutation in a gene is made increasingly severe by a subsequent mutation (SBO:0000501).

      • GENETIC_SUPPRESSION

        public static final URI GENETIC_SUPPRESSION
        Genetic suppression is said to have occurred when the phenotypic effect of an initial mutation in a gene is less severe, or entirely negated, by a subsequent mutation (SBO:0000500).

      • SYNTHETIC_LETHALITY

        public static final URI SYNTHETIC_LETHALITY
        Synthetic lethality is said to have occurred where gene mutations, each of which map to a separate locus, fail to complement in an offspring to correct a phenotype, as would be expected (SBO:0000502).

      • MOLECULAR_INTERACTION

        public static final URI MOLECULAR_INTERACTION
        Relationship between molecular entities, based on contacts, direct or indirect (SBO:0000344).

      • PROTEIN_COMPLEX_FORMATION

        public static final URI PROTEIN_COMPLEX_FORMATION
        The process by which two or more proteins interact non-covalently to form a protein complex (SBO:0000526).

      • OMITTED_PROCESS

        public static final URI OMITTED_PROCESS
        One or more processes that are not represented in certain representations or interpretations of a model (SBO:0000397).

      • PHENOTYPE

        public static final URI PHENOTYPE
        A biochemical network can generate phenotypes or affects biological processes (SBO:0000358). Such processes can take place at different levels and are independent of the biochemical network itself.

      • STATE_VARIABLE_ASSIGNMENT

        public static final URI STATE_VARIABLE_ASSIGNMENT
        Assignment of a state or a value to a state variable, characteristic or property, of a biological entity (SBO:0000464).

      • PETRI_NET_TRANSITION

        public static final URI PETRI_NET_TRANSITION
        A process that can modify the state of petri net 'places' (SBO:0000591).

      • UNCERTAIN_PROCESS

        public static final URI UNCERTAIN_PROCESS
        An equivocal or conjectural process, whose existence is assumed but not proven (SBO:0000396).

      • RELATIONSHIP

        public static final URI RELATIONSHIP
        Connectedness between entities and/or interactions representing their relatedness or influence (SBO:0000374).

      • CONTROL

        public static final URI CONTROL
        Modification of the execution of an event or a process (SBO:0000168).

      • ALLOSTERIC_CONTROL

        public static final URI ALLOSTERIC_CONTROL
        Regulation of the influence of a reaction participant by binding an effector to a binding site of the participant different of the site of the participant conveying the influence (SBO:0000239).

      • CONSUMPTION

        public static final URI CONSUMPTION
        Decrease in amount of a material or conceptual entity (SBO:0000394).

      • INHIBITION

        public static final URI INHIBITION
        Negative modulation of the execution of a process (SBO:0000169).

      • ABSOLUTE_INHIBITION

        public static final URI ABSOLUTE_INHIBITION
        Control that precludes the execution of a process (SBO:0000407).

      • PRODUCTION

        public static final URI PRODUCTION
        Generation of a material or conceptual entity (SBO:0000393).

      • STIMULATION

        public static final URI STIMULATION
        Positive modulation of the execution of a process (SBO:0000170).

      • ABSOLUTE_STIMULATION

        public static final URI ABSOLUTE_STIMULATION
        Control that always triggers the controlled process (SBO:0000411).

      • CATALYSIS

        public static final URI CATALYSIS
        Modification of the velocity of a reaction by lowering the energy of the transition state (SBO:0000172).

      • NECESSARY_STIMULATION

        public static final URI NECESSARY_STIMULATION
        Control that is necessary to the execution of a process (SBO:0000171).

      • EQUIVALENCE

        public static final URI EQUIVALENCE
        Term to signify those material or conceptual entities that are identical in some respect within a frame of reference (SBO:0000392).

      • LOGICAL_COMBINATION

        public static final URI LOGICAL_COMBINATION
        Combining the influence of several entities or events in a unique influence (SBO:0000237).

      • AND

        public static final URI AND
        All the preceding events or participating entities are necessary to perform the control (SBO:0000173).

      • NOT

        public static final URI NOT
        The preceding event or participating entity cannot participate to the control (SBO:0000238).

      • OR

        public static final URI OR
        Any of the preceding events or participating entities are necessary to perform the control (SBO:0000174).

      • XOR

        public static final URI XOR
        Only one of the preceding events or participating entities can perform the control at one time (SBO:0000175).

      • LOGICAL_RELATIONSHIP

        public static final URI LOGICAL_RELATIONSHIP
        Relationship between entities (material or conceptual) and logical operators, or between logical operators themselves (SBO:0000398).

      • POSITIONAL_RELATIONSHIP

        public static final URI POSITIONAL_RELATIONSHIP
        The connectedness between entities as related by their position (SBO:0000413).

      • CIS

        public static final URI CIS
        Positional relationship between entities on the same strand (e.g. in DNA), or on the same side (SBO:0000414).

      • CONTAINMENT

        public static final URI CONTAINMENT
        An entity that is a subset of another entity or object (SBO:0000469).

      • TRANS

        public static final URI TRANS
        Positional relationship between entities on different sides, or strands (SBO:0000415).

      • FUNCTIONAL_COMPARTMENT

        public static final URI FUNCTIONAL_COMPARTMENT
        Logical or physical subset of the event space that contains pools, that is sets of participants considered identical when it comes to the event they are involved into (SBO:0000289). A compartment can have any number of dimensions, including 0, and be of any size including null.

      • MODIFIER

        public static final URI MODIFIER
        Substance that changes the velocity of a process without itself being consumed or transformed by the reaction (SBO:0000019).

      • DUAL_ACTIVITY_MODIFIER

        public static final URI DUAL_ACTIVITY_MODIFIER
        A modifier that can exhibit either inhibitory or stimulatory effects on a process depending on the context in which it occurs (SBO:0000595). For example, the observed effect may be dependent upon the concentration of the modifier.

      • INHIBITOR

        public static final URI INHIBITOR
        Substance that decreases the probability of a chemical reaction without itself being consumed or transformed by the reaction (SBO:0000020).

      • COMPETITIVE_INHIBITOR

        public static final URI COMPETITIVE_INHIBITOR
        Substance that decreases the probability of a chemical reaction, without itself being consumed or transformed by the reaction, by stericaly hindering the interaction between reactants (SBO:0000206).

      • NON_COMPETITIVE_INHIBITOR

        public static final URI NON_COMPETITIVE_INHIBITOR
        Substance that decreases the probability of a chemical reaction, without itself being consumed or transformed by the reaction, and without sterically hindering the interaction between reactants (SBO:0000207).

      • SILENCER

        public static final URI SILENCER
        A silencer is a modifier which acts in a manner that completely prevents an event or process from occurring (SBO:0000597). For example, a silencer in gene expression is usually a transcription factor that binds a DNA sequence in such a way as to completely prevent the binding of RNA polymerase, and thus fully suppresses transcription.

      • MODIFIER_OF_UNKNOWN_ACTIVITY

        public static final URI MODIFIER_OF_UNKNOWN_ACTIVITY
        A modifier whose activity is not known or has not been specified (SBO:0000596).

      • STIMULATOR

        public static final URI STIMULATOR
        Substance that accelerates the velocity of a chemical reaction without itself being consumed or transformed (SBO:0000459).

      • CATALYST

        public static final URI CATALYST
        Substance that accelerates the velocity of a chemical reaction without itself being consumed or transformed (SBO:0000013). This effect is achieved by lowering the free energy of the transition state.

      • ENZYMATIC_CATALYST

        public static final URI ENZYMATIC_CATALYST
        A substance that accelerates the velocity of a chemical reaction without itself being consumed or transformed, by lowering the free energy of the transition state (SBO:0000460). The substance acting as a catalyst is an enzyme.

      • ESSENTIAL_ACTIVATOR

        public static final URI ESSENTIAL_ACTIVATOR
        A substance that is absolutely required for occurrence and stimulation of a reaction (SBO:0000461).

      • BINDING_ACTIVATOR

        public static final URI BINDING_ACTIVATOR
        An essential activator that affects the apparent value of the Michaelis constant(s) (SBO:0000535).

      • CATALYTIC_ACTIVATOR

        public static final URI CATALYTIC_ACTIVATOR
        An essential activator that affects the apparent value of the catalytic constant (SBO:0000534).

      • SPECIFIC_ACTIVATOR

        public static final URI SPECIFIC_ACTIVATOR
        An essential activator that affects the apparent value of the specificity constant (SBO:0000533). Mechanistically, the activator would need to be bound before reactant and product binding can take place.

      • NON_ESSENTIAL_ACTIVATOR

        public static final URI NON_ESSENTIAL_ACTIVATOR
        An activator which is not necessary for an enzymatic reaction, but whose presence will further increase enzymatic activity (SBO:0000462).

      • POTENTIATOR

        public static final URI POTENTIATOR
        Substance that increases the probability of a chemical reaction without itself being consumed or transformed by the reaction (SBO:0000021). This effect is achieved by increasing the difference of free energy between the reactant(s) and the product(s).

      • NEUTRAL_PARTICIPANT

        public static final URI NEUTRAL_PARTICIPANT
        A participant whose presence does not alter the velocity of a process or event (SBO:0000594).

      • PRODUCT

        public static final URI PRODUCT
        Substance that is produced in a reaction (SBO:0000011). In a chemical equation the Products are the elements or compounds on the right hand side of the reaction equation. A product can be produced and consumed by the same reaction, its global quantity remaining unchanged.

      • SIDE_PRODUCT

        public static final URI SIDE_PRODUCT
        A substance that is produced in a chemical reaction but is not itself the primary product or focus of that reaction (SBO:0000603). Examples include, but are not limited to, currency compounds such as ATP, NADPH and protons.

      • PROMOTER

        public static final URI PROMOTER
        A region of DNA to which various transcription factors and RNA polymerase must bind in order to initiate transcription for a gene (SBO:0000598).

      • REACTANT

        public static final URI REACTANT
        Substance consumed by a chemical reaction (SBO:0000010). Reactants react with each other to form the products of a chemical reaction. In a chemical equation the Reactants are the elements or compounds on the left hand side of the reaction equation. A reactant can be consumed and produced by the same reaction, its global quantity remaining unchanged.

      • INTERACTOR

        public static final URI INTERACTOR
        Entity participating in a physical or functional interaction (SBO:0000336).

      • SUBSTRATE

        public static final URI SUBSTRATE
        Molecule which is acted upon by an enzyme (SBO:0000015). The substrate binds with the enzyme's active site, and the enzyme catalyzes a chemical reaction involving the substrate.

      • SIDE_SUBSTRATE

        public static final URI SIDE_SUBSTRATE
        A substance that is consumed in a chemical reaction but is not itself the primary substrate or focus of that reaction (SBO:0000604). Examples include, but are not limited to, currency compounds such as ATP, NADPH and protons.
